				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Can you give gear to charmed stuff?<a name="51461"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 3:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mobs used to accept nodrop items... then kunark came out.  A trivial OT quest resulted in the workman's sledgemallet, a nodrop 2hb with a proc... self gate to overthere.  To put it mildly, the server's didn't like mobs trying to port to overthere from other zones...
<br />

<br />
People also used to give slow/crappy 2h weapons to mobs to &quot;nerf&quot; their DPS output (pre-kunark, monk in rathe mtns + rusty scythe = easy instead of very hard), which also got fixed/nerfed so that weapons could only improve mob melee, not reduce it below a default value.  Then some nasty fellows thought it might be fun to give mobs like pofear's CT (chanters can be nonkos to him with the right diety and illusion) things like paw stun whips, which he dual wielded and chain proc'ed... 
<br />

<br />
Fast forward to today; most npc's won't accept items at all, unless they are for a quest it is involved in, or if they are pets.  So the answer is yes, you can give gear to charmed mobs, including armor (ogres in potac will wear the mage summoned armor, and look like they are wearing full rubicite!), weapons (dual wielding pookas are blenders of death), haste items (muzzle of mardu, etc.), and light sources.  You don't have to worry about giving Lady Gore your drood epic anymore tho. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />(inside joke, it happened).
<br />

<br />
Think that's all correct anyway.  And I deny everything. ;)
<br />
RdT.</span></td>
